From Privilage mode ----->
  > enable
  > configure terminal
  > enable ?
  > enable secred (password u want to enter)   more secure 
  > enable password (password u want to enter) and exit
  > show run (to see details) 
  
From User mode ----->
  > enable
  > configure terminal
  > line console 0
  > password (password u want to enter)
  > login
  > end
  
From User mode add banner----->
  > enable
  > configure terminal
  > banner motd $Please login$
  
Remotely access  ----->
  > enable
  > configure terminal
  > line vty 0 15
  > password (password u want to enter)
  > login
  then from commandprompt 
  > telnet + that ip address
  
Encrypt password ----->
  > enable
  > configure terminal
  > do show run
  > service password-encryption
  > do show run
  
